contentrichtext.text: '''OES''' can stand for: * [[Bureau of Oceans and International Environmental and Scientific Affairs]] * [[Old East Slavic language]] * [[Old English Sheepdog]] - a breed of herding dog often kept as a pet * [[Novell Open Enterprise Server|Open Enterprise Server]] - [[Novell]]'s amalgam of [[NetWare]] and [[Linux]] * [[Order of the Eastern Star]] - a fraternal organisation * [[Oregon Episcopal School]] - an independent, PreK-12 college-preparatory school in Portland, Oregon * [[Office of Emergency Services]] - a governmental agency in charge of emergency & disaster planning and management * [[Occupational Employment Statistics]] - The Occupational Employment Statistics (OES) program produces employment and wage estimates for over 800 occupations * [[Open EMS Suite By Nokia Siemens Networks]] - A management software platform by Nokia Siemens Networks * [[Optical Emissions Spectrometer]] - Optical Emissions Spectrometer - an instrument for testing chemical composition of metals * [[O]] - the plural for the name of the letter "O", 'oes' * [[Ordo Equitum Solis]] - French/Italian alternative music band * Original Equipment Supply/suppliers {{disambig}}
